==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mannite
<hw>Man"nite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Same as
<er>mannitol</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A sweet white efflorescence from
dried fronds of kelp, especially from those of the <spn>Laminaria
saccharina</spn>, or devil's apron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mannitic</ent>⟦br⟧
